<subSubSection id="2BDF36FFFFFBE119D1EAB4250BA8F920" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="637A6574FFFBE119D1EAB4250BA8F920" blockId="1.[151,1437,1178,1673]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D1EAB4250907FAC1" bold="true" box="[199,324,1358,1384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
female dorsal shield smooth, with usually 37 pairs of setae (
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D525B4240C62FAC0" box="[1032,1057,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">r5</emphasis>
missing in all specimens and 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D4ADB4240DDFFAC0" box="[1408,1436,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">S1</emphasis>
missing in four of 
<specimenCount id="75C3AEFDFFFBE119D042B4180A51FA27" box="[367,530,1395,1422]" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
), including two pairs of extra 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D25DB4180BCDFA25" box="[880,910,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Px</emphasis>
setae and one unpaired extra 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D5C5B4180D42FA25" box="[1256,1281,1395,1420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Jx</emphasis>
seta between 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D1BAB4FC08F1FA18" box="[151,178,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">J4</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D1C0B4FC0944FA18" box="[237,263,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">J5</emphasis>
; setae longer than distance to the respective closest setae, except 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D52CB4FC0C55FA18" box="[1025,1046,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">j1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D50AB4FC0C03FA18" box="[1063,1088,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">z1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D57DB4FC0C28FA18" box="[1104,1131,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">J5</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D58BB4FC0C87FA18" box="[1190,1220,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Z4</emphasis>
which are shorter; most of setae with basal asymmetric lobe. Unsclerotised lateroventral idiosomal cuticle with eight pairs of lightly serrate setae (
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D002B4B5090BFA51" box="[303,328,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">r6</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D078B4B409E2FA50" box="[341,417,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">
<specimenCode id="3363CD0FFFFBE119D078B4B40937FA50" box="[341,372,1503,1529]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">R1</specimenCode>
– 
<specimenCode id="3363CD0FFFFBE119D0AFB4B409E2FA50" box="[386,417,1503,1529]" collectionCode="R" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">R5</specimenCode>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D083B4B409A1FA50" box="[430,482,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">UR1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D0C2B4B40A61FA50" box="[495,546,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">UR2</emphasis>
). Epigynal shield slightly overlapping the anal shield, ornamented with “ 
<collectionCode id="05D4FDB1FFFBE119D461B4B40D20FA50" box="[1356,1379,1503,1529]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
” and “inverted 
<collectionCode id="05D4FDB1FFFBE119D02AB768095EF9B4" box="[263,285,1539,1565]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="1" pageNumber="568" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
” shaped pattern and with three pairs of setae (
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D21CB7680B12F9B4" box="[817,849,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">st5</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D24CB7680BC4F9B4" box="[865,903,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Jv1</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D2BAB7680B82F9B4" box="[919,961,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Zv1</emphasis>
) which are very close to the margin. One pair of metapodal platelets. Ten pairs of opisthogastric setae (
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D26CB74C0BDEF9E8" box="[833,925,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Jv1–Jv5</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D287B74C0C4FF9E8" box="[938,1036,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Zv1–Zv5</emphasis>
); 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D509B74C0C0DF9E8" box="[1060,1102,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Zv1</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D5AEB74C0CEEF9E8" box="[1155,1197,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Zv2</emphasis>
smooth and 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D417B74C0D22F9E8" box="[1338,1377,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Jv4</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D443B74C0DD5F9E8" box="[1390,1430,1575,1601]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Jv5</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="51B1B966FFFBE119D1BAB72008BAF9CC" box="[151,249,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="568">Zv3–Zv5</emphasis>
with barely distinguishable serration. Epistome subtriangular, with margin undulate and smooth. Fixed and movable cheliceral digits each with one tooth in addition to the apical tooth.
</paragraph>
